class DepthSeparableConv2d(nn.Module):
    def __init__(self, in_channels, out_channels, kernel_size=3, padding=1, **kwargs):
        super(DepthSeparableConv2d, self).__init__()
        self.depthwise = nn.Conv2d(in_channels, in_channels, kernel_size=kernel_size, padding=padding, groups=in_channels, **kwargs)
        self.pointwise = nn.Conv2d(in_channels, out_channels, kernel_size=1)

    def forward(self, x1):
        x2 = self.depthwise(x1)
        x3 = self.pointwise(x2)
        return x3
    
    
class AddGaussianNoise:
    def __init__(self, mean=0., std=1., p=1.):
        self.std = std
        self.mean = mean
        self.p = p
        
    def __call__(self, tensor):
        if np.random.rand() > self.p:
            return tensor
        
        return tensor + (torch.randn(tensor.size()) * self.std + self.mean) * torch.randn([1])
    
    def __repr__(self):
        return self.__class__.__name__ + f'({self.mean = }, {self.std = })'


class EarlyStopping:
    def __init__(self, tolerance=5, min_delta=0.):
        self.tolerance = tolerance
        self.min_delta = min_delta
        self.best_loss = 1e9
        self.counter = 0
        self.early_stop = False

    def step(self, val_loss):
        if (val_loss - self.best_loss) > self.min_delta:
            self.counter += 1
            if self.counter >= self.tolerance:  
                self.early_stop = True

        self.best_loss = min(val_loss, self.best_loss)
    
    def __bool__(self):
        return self.early_stop
    
class SaveOnlyBestModel:
    def __init__(self, model_to_save: nn.Module, model_name_to_save='', **kwargs):
        self.best_val_loss = 1e9
        self.model_to_save = model_to_save
        self.model_name_to_save = model_name_to_save
        self.kwargs = kwargs

    def step(self, val_loss):
        if (val_loss - self.best_val_loss) < 0.:
            save_model(self.model_to_save, self.model_name_to_save, **self.kwargs)
        self.best_val_loss = min(val_loss, self.best_val_loss)


def progress_bar(n_iter, n_total, prefix='Progress: ', suffix='', length=55, fill='', lost='-', percent=True):
    percent = f"{100 * (n_iter / float(n_total)) :.1f}% " if percent else ""
    filled_length = round(length * n_iter // n_total)
    bar = fill * filled_length + lost * (length - filled_length)
    print(f'\r{prefix}[{n_iter}/{n_total}] |{bar}| {percent}{suffix}', end=' ' * 10)
    if n_iter == n_total:
        print()


def np_softmax(logits):
    assert len(logits.shape) == 2
    s = np.max(logits, axis=1)
    s = s[:, np.newaxis]
    e_x = np.exp(logits - s)
    div = np.sum(e_x, axis=1)
    div = div[:, np.newaxis]
    return e_x / div


def save_model(model_: nn.Module, name="", weights_model=False, all_model=True):
    name = name if name else model_.name
    if weights_model:
        torch.save(model_.state_dict(), f"models/{name}_weights.pth")
    if all_model:
        torch.save(model_, f"models/{name}.pth")

def load_model_weights(model_class, name="") -> nn.Module:
    name = name if name else model_class.base_name
    model_ = model_class()
    model_.load_state_dict(torch.load(f"models/{name}_weights.pth"))
    model_.to(device).eval()
    return model_

def load_model(name: str) -> nn.Module:
    model_ = torch.load(f"models/{name}.pth").to(device).eval()
    return model_


def show_history(history_):
    plt.figure(figsize=(13, 5))
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.plot(history_["train_losses"], label='Training loss')
    plt.plot(history_["val_losses"], label='Validation loss')
    plt.legend(frameon=False)
    plt.title("Loss on training")
    
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.plot(history_["train_accuracy"], label='Training accuracy')
    plt.plot(history_["val_accuracy"], label='Validation accuracy')
    plt.legend(frameon=False)
    plt.title("Accuracy on training")
    plt.show()
    
def get_model_prediction(model_for_test: nn.Module, loader: torch.utils.data.DataLoader, augmentation=None):
    model_for_test.eval()
    if augmentation:
        raise "Augmentation must be None for best accuracy"
    with torch.no_grad():
        y_pred = y_true = None
        for i, (images, labels) in enumerate(loader):
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)
            labels = F.one_hot(labels, num_classes=3)
            # if augmentation:
            #     images = augmentation(images)
            if y_pred is None:
                y_pred = model_for_test(images).detach().cpu().numpy()
                y_true = labels.detach().cpu().numpy()
            else:
                y_pred = np.vstack([y_pred, model_for_test(images).detach().cpu().numpy()])
                y_true = np.vstack([y_true, labels.detach().cpu().numpy()])
            progress_bar(i+1, len(loader), prefix='Testing: ', length=25)

    y_pred = np_softmax(y_pred)
    y_true_class = np.argmax(y_true, axis=-1)
    y_pred_class = np.argmax(y_pred, axis=-1)
    # y_pred_onehot = F.one_hot(torch.argmax(torch.Tensor(y_pred_class), dim=-1)).numpy()
    return y_pred_class, y_pred, y_true_class, y_true
    
def test_model(model_for_test: nn.Module, loader: torch.utils.data.DataLoader, augmentation=None, history_to_show=None):
    if history_to_show:
        show_history(history_to_show)

    y_pred_class, y_pred, y_true_class, y_true = get_model_prediction(model_for_test, loader, augmentation=augmentation)
    y_pred_onehot = F.one_hot(torch.Tensor(y_pred_class).to(torch.int64)).numpy()
    print()  # np.round(y_pred[:15], 3)
    print(sklearn.metrics.classification_report(y_true, y_pred_onehot, target_names=list(labels_map_reversed.keys())))
    print(f"Accuracy test:  {sklearn.metrics.accuracy_score(y_true, y_pred_onehot) :.4f}")
    
def make_output_csv_file(model_for_test: nn.Module, loader: torch.utils.data.DataLoader, augmentation=None, fname="outputs"):
    y_pred_class, y_pred, y_true_class, y_true = get_model_prediction(model_for_test, loader, augmentation=augmentation)

    print(np.arange(0, len(y_pred_class)).shape, y_pred_class.shape)
    with open(f"{fname}.csv", 'w', newline='', encoding='utf-8') as f:
        writer = csv.writer(f, delimiter=',')
        writer.writerow(['id', 'predict_feature'])
        for row in zip(np.arange(0, len(y_pred_class)), y_pred_class):
            writer.writerow(row)
    print(f"{fname}.csv created!")
    return y_pred_class
    
    
def show_from_loader(loader: torch.utils.data.DataLoader, augmentation=None, model_for_test=None, rows=1, cols=8, color='gray'):
    if isinstance(loader, torch.utils.data.DataLoader):
        imgs, labels = next(iter(loader))
    else:
        imgs, labels = loader[:rows * cols]
        
    imgs, labels = imgs[:rows*cols], labels[:rows*cols].numpy()
    
    if model_for_test:
        y_pred = np.argmax(F.softmax(model_for_test(imgs.to(device)), dim=-1).detach().cpu().numpy(), axis=-1)
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(int(2.3*cols), int(2.7*rows)))
    for i in range(cols*rows):
        plt.subplot(rows, cols, i + 1)
        image = imgs[i]
        if augmentation:
            image = augmentation(image)
        image = image.numpy().transpose((1, 2, 0))
        image = np.clip(image, 0., 1.)
        plt.imshow(image, cmap=color)
        plt.xticks([])
        plt.yticks([])
        if model_for_test:
            plt.title(f"{labels_map[int(y_pred[i])]}({int(labels[i])})", c=('g' if labels[i] == y_pred[i] else 'r'))
        else:
            plt.title(labels_map[int(labels[i])])
    
    plt.show()
    print(f"Min={imgs.min()} Max={imgs.max()} Mean={imgs.mean()} Std={imgs.std()}")

def show_one_test(loader: torch.utils.data.DataLoader, model_for_test: nn.Module, augmentation=None):
    imgs, labels = next(iter(loader))
    idx = np.random.randint(0, len(imgs))
    img, label = imgs[idx], labels[idx]
    if augmentation:
        img = augmentation(img)
    
    model_out = F.softmax(model_for_test(img[None, :, :, :].to(device)), dim=-1).detach().cpu().numpy()
    y_pred, y_true = np.argmax(model_out), int(label.numpy())
    
    color = 'g' if y_true == y_pred else 'r'
    
    plt.figure(figsize=(14, 4))
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 1)
    plt.imshow(img.numpy().transpose((1, 2, 0)), cmap='gray')
    plt.title(f"{labels_map[y_true]}", c=color)
    
    class_names = list(labels_map.values())  # print([f"{class_names[i]}" for i in range(3)])
    plt.subplot(1, 2, 2)
    plt.bar([class_names[i] for i in range(3)], np.squeeze(model_out) * 100, color=color, width=0.7)
    plt.xlabel("")
    plt.ylabel("   %")
    plt.title(" ")
    plt.show()

Train cycle

In[5]:
def train(model_training: nn.Module, optim: torch.optim.Optimizer, loss_fn, epochs=1000,
          augmentation=None, callbacks=None, options=None):
    train_losses, val_losses = [], []
    train_accuracy, val_accuracy = [], []
    
    # Model Training
    model_training.train()
    for epoch in range(1, epochs+1):
        start_time = time.time()
        train_loss = train_total_correct = 0
        for i, (images, labels) in enumerate(train_loader):
            # CutMix & MixUp
            if options["batch_cut_mix_up"]:
                images, labels = options["batch_cut_mix_up"](images, labels)
            # Augmentation
            if augmentation:
                images = augmentation(images)
            images, labels = images.to(device), labels.to(device)
            # Prevent accumulation of gradients
            optim.zero_grad()
            # Make predictions
            outputs = model_training(images)
            loss = loss_fn(outputs, labels)
            # Backprop
            loss.backward()
            # Gradient Clip
            if options["grad_clipping_value"]:
                torch.nn.utils.clip_grad_value_(model_training.parameters(), options["grad_clipping_value"])
            # Return labels
            if options["batch_cut_mix_up"]:
                labels = torch.argmax(labels, dim=-1)
            # Update params
            optim.step()
    
            train_loss += loss.item()
            
            # Metrics - Accuracy
            correct_count = (torch.max(outputs.data, 1)[1] == labels).sum().detach().cpu().numpy()
            train_total_correct += correct_count

            progress_bar(i, len(train_loader), prefix=f"Epoch {epoch} train: ",
                         suffix=f"loss: {loss.item() :.3f}\taccuracy: {correct_count / len(labels):.3f}")
            
    
        # Model Validation
        with torch.no_grad():
            model_training.train(False)
            val_loss = val_total_correct = 0
            
            for i, (val_images, val_labels) in enumerate(val_loader):
                val_images, val_labels = val_images.to(device), val_labels.to(device)
                # Forward propagation
                outputs = model_training(val_images)
                loss = loss_fn(outputs, val_labels)
                val_loss += loss.item()

                # Metrics - Accuracy
                correct_count = (torch.max(outputs.data, 1)[1] == val_labels).sum().detach().cpu().numpy()
                val_total_correct += correct_count
                
                progress_bar(i, len(val_loader), prefix=f"Epoch {epoch} val: ",
                             suffix=f"loss: {loss.item() :.3f}\taccuracy: {correct_count / len(val_labels):.3f}")

        model_training.train()
        
        train_losses.append(train_loss / len(train_loader))
        val_losses.append(val_loss / len(val_loader))

        val_accuracy.append(val_total_correct / len(val_loader.dataset))
        train_accuracy.append(train_total_correct / len(train_loader.dataset))
        
        progress_bar(len(train_loader), len(train_loader), prefix=f"Epoch {epoch} ({time.time()-start_time :.0f} sec): ", length=10, percent=False,
                     suffix=f"loss: {train_losses[-1] :.4f}\taccuracy: {train_accuracy[-1] :.3f}\t"
                            f"val_loss: {val_losses[-1] :.4f}\tval_accuracy: {val_accuracy[-1] :.3f}\t" +
                            (f"Lr (e-3): {callbacks['lr_scheduler'].optimizer.param_groups[0]['lr'] * 1e3:.2f}"
                             if callbacks and callbacks.get("lr_scheduler") else ""))
        
        if callbacks:
            if "early_stopping" in callbacks.keys():
                callbacks["early_stopping"].step(val_losses[-1])
                if callbacks["early_stopping"]:
                    print("INFO: Early stopping!")
                    break
            if "lr_scheduler" in callbacks.keys():
                callbacks["lr_scheduler"].step(val_losses[-1])
            if "save_best_model" in callbacks.keys():
                callbacks["save_best_model"].step(val_losses[-1])


    model_training.train(False)
    return {"train_losses": train_losses,
            "val_losses": val_losses,
            "val_accuracy": val_accuracy,
            "train_accuracy": train_accuracy,}

Model architecture

In[6]:
class Model_SqueezeNeXt(nn.Module):
    # https://sh-tsang.medium.com/reading-squeezenext-hardware-aware-neural-network-design-image-classification-3fc8d1d3f76
    # https://github.com/osmr/imgclsmob/blob/c03fa67de3c9e454e9b6d35fe9cbb6b15c28fda7/pytorch/pytorchcv/models/squeezenext.py
    # https://arxiv.org/pdf/1803.10615v2.pdf
    class SqueezeNeXtUnit(nn.Module):
        def __init__(self,
                     in_channels,
                     out_channels,
                     stride):
            super().__init__()
            if stride == 2:
                reduction_den = 1
                self.resize_identity = True
            elif in_channels > out_channels:
                reduction_den = 4
                self.resize_identity = True
            else:
                reduction_den = 2
                self.resize_identity = False
                
            self.use_bias = False
            self.act = nn.ReLU(inplace=True)
            
            self.conv_x5 = nn.Sequential(
                # Conv 1 (1x1)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den),
                          kernel_size=1, bias=self.use_bias, stride=stride),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=(in_channels // reduction_den)), self.act,
                # Conv 2 (1x1)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den), out_channels=(in_channels // (2 * reduction_den)),
                          kernel_size=1, bias=self.use_bias),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=(in_channels // (2 * reduction_den))), self.act,
                # Conv 3 (1x3)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=(in_channels // (2 * reduction_den)), out_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den),
                          kernel_size=(1, 3), padding=(0, 1), bias=self.use_bias),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=(in_channels // reduction_den)), self.act,
                # Conv 4 (3x1)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den), out_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den),
                          kernel_size=(3, 1), padding=(1, 0), bias=self.use_bias),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=(in_channels // reduction_den)), self.act,
                # Conv 5 (1x1)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den), out_channels=out_channels,
                          kernel_size=1, bias=self.use_bias),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=out_channels), self.act,
            )

            if self.resize_identity:
                self.identity_conv = nn.Sequential(
                    nn.Conv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=out_channels, kernel_size=1,
                              stride=stride, bias=self.use_bias),
                    nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=out_channels), self.act
                )
    
        def forward(self, x):
            if self.resize_identity:
                identity = self.identity_conv(x)
            else:
                identity = x
            x = self.conv_x5(x)
            x = x + identity
            return self.act(x)

    def __init__(self, name="v1",      # Name iteration of model
                 width_scale=1.,       # Wide of model
                 layers=[2, 4, 14, 1]  # From original SqNxt-23
                 ):
        super().__init__()
        self.name = f"{width_scale:.1f}-SqNxt-{sum(layers)+2}_{name}"
        
        # SqNxt-23v5
        num_classes = 3
        init_block_channels = int(64 * width_scale)
        final_block_channels = int(128 * width_scale)
        channels_per_layers = [32, 64, 128, 256]
        channels = [[int(ci * width_scale)] * li for (ci, li) in zip(channels_per_layers, layers)]
        print(self.name, [init_block_channels], *channels, [final_block_channels])
        
        # Make arch
        self.features = nn.Sequential()
        self.features.add_module("first_block", nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(1, init_block_channels, kernel_size=5, stride=2),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(init_block_channels), nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3, stride=2, ceil_mode=True),
        ))
        
        in_channels = init_block_channels
        for i, channels_per_stage in enumerate(channels):
            stage = nn.Sequential()
            for j, out_channels in enumerate(channels_per_stage):
                stride = 2 if (j == 0) and (i != 0) else 1
                stage.add_module(f"unit_{j + 1}", Model_SqueezeNeXt.SqueezeNeXtUnit(
                    in_channels=in_channels,
                    out_channels=out_channels,
                    stride=stride))
                in_channels = out_channels
            self.features.add_module(f"stage_{i + 1}", stage)
        
        self.features.add_module("final_block", nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=final_block_channels, kernel_size=1, bias=True),
            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1)),
            nn.Flatten()
        ))

        self.output = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(in_features=final_block_channels, out_features=num_classes)
        )

    def forward(self, x):
        x = transform_model_forward(x)
        x = self.features(x)
        x = self.output(x)
        return x

class Model_CNN(nn.Module):
    base_name = "model_test_V1"
    def __init__(self, name=base_name):
        super().__init__()
        self.name = name
        
        self.layer1 = nn.Sequential(  # 256 - 64
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=1, out_channels=32, kernel_size=4, padding=1, bias=False),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(32),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout2d(p=0.08),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2),
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=32, out_channels=64, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(64),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout2d(p=0.2),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2),
        )
        self.layer2 = nn.Sequential(  # 64 - 32
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=64, out_channels=64, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(64),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout2d(p=0.2),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2),
        )
        self.layer3 = nn.Sequential(  # 32 - 16
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=64, out_channels=96, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(96),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout2d(p=0.2),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2),
        )
        self.layer4 = nn.Sequential(  # 16 - 4
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=96, out_channels=128, kernel_size=2, padding=1, bias=False),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(128),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout2d(p=0.15),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=2, stride=2),
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=128, out_channels=196, kernel_size=2, padding=1, bias=False),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(196),
            nn.ReLU(),
            nn.Dropout2d(p=0.15),
            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1)),
        )
        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(196, 128)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(128, 64)
        self.fc3 = nn.Linear(64, 3)
        self.bn1 = nn.BatchNorm1d(128)
        self.bn2 = nn.BatchNorm1d(64)
        
        self.fc_dropout = nn.Dropout(p=0.17)

    def forward(self, x1):
        x2 = self.layer1(x1)
        x3 = self.layer2(x2)
        x4 = self.layer3(x3)
        x5 = self.layer4(x4)
        
        f1 = torch.flatten(x5, start_dim=1)
        f2 = self.fc_dropout(F.relu(self.bn1(self.fc1(f1))))
        f3 = self.fc_dropout(F.relu(self.bn2(self.fc2(f2))))
        logits = self.fc3(f3)
        return logits
    
class Model_ResNet_V2(nn.Module):
    base_name = "res_net_v2"
    # https://medium.com/@ibtedaazeem/understanding-resnet-architecture-a-deep-dive-into-residual-neural-network-2c792e6537a9
    # https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/residual-networks-resnet-deep-learning/
    # https://arxiv.org/pdf/1512.03385.pdf
    class Block(nn.Module):
        def __init__(self, in_channels: int, x2_channels=False, x2_stride=False):
            super().__init__()
            out_channels = in_channels * 2 if x2_channels else in_channels
            self.conv1 = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=out_channels, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False,
                                   stride=2 if x2_stride else 1)
            self.bn1 = nn.BatchNorm2d(out_channels)
            self.conv2 = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=out_channels, out_channels=out_channels, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False)
            self.bn2 = nn.BatchNorm2d(out_channels)
            
            self.dropout2d = nn.Dropout2d(p=0.1)
            self.res_permute = x2_channels or x2_stride
            self.in_channels = in_channels
            if x2_channels or x2_stride:
                self.res_conv = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=out_channels, kernel_size=1, stride=2 if x2_stride else 1)

        def forward(self, x):
            res_x = x
            if self.res_permute:
                res_x = self.res_conv(res_x)

            x = self.conv1(x)
            x = F.relu(self.bn1(x))
            x = self.conv2(x)
            x = self.bn2(x)
            x_out = x + res_x
            return self.dropout2d(F.relu(x_out))
            # return F.relu(x_out)
    
    def __init__(self, name=base_name):
        super().__init__()
        self.name = name
        
        self.first_layer = nn.Sequential(  # 256 - 128
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=1, out_channels=32, kernel_size=7, padding=3, bias=False, stride=2),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(32),
            nn.ReLU(),
            # nn.Dropout2d(p=0.08),
        )

        self.blocks = nn.Sequential(
            # self.Block(in_channels=32),  # 128
            self.Block(in_channels=32, x2_channels=True, x2_stride=True),  # 64
            self.Block(in_channels=64),
            self.Block(in_channels=64, x2_channels=True, x2_stride=True),  # 32
            self.Block(in_channels=128),
            self.Block(in_channels=128, x2_channels=True, x2_stride=True),  # 16
            self.Block(in_channels=256, x2_channels=False, x2_stride=True),  # 8
        )
        
        self.output_layer = nn.Sequential(  # 1
            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1)),
            nn.Flatten()
            # nn.Dropout2d(p=0.08),
        )
        
        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(256, 128)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(128, 3)
        self.bn1 = nn.BatchNorm1d(128)
        self.fc_dropout = nn.Dropout(p=0.17)

    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.first_layer(x)
        x = self.blocks(x)
        x = self.output_layer(x)
        x = self.fc_dropout(F.relu(self.bn1(self.fc1(x))))
        logits = self.fc2(x)
        return logits
    
class Model_ResNet_V3(nn.Module):
    base_name = "res_net_v3_"
    # https://medium.com/@ibtedaazeem/understanding-resnet-architecture-a-deep-dive-into-residual-neural-network-2c792e6537a9
    # https://www.geeksforgeeks.org/residual-networks-resnet-deep-learning/
    # https://arxiv.org/pdf/1512.03385.pdf
    class Block(nn.Module):
        def __init__(self, in_channels: int, x2_channels=False, x2_stride=False):
            super().__init__()
            out_channels = in_channels * 2 if x2_channels else in_channels
            self.conv1 = DepthSeparableConv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=out_channels, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False,
                                   stride=2 if x2_stride else 1)
            self.bn1 = nn.BatchNorm2d(out_channels)
            self.conv2 = DepthSeparableConv2d(in_channels=out_channels, out_channels=out_channels, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False)
            self.bn2 = nn.BatchNorm2d(out_channels)
            
            self.dropout2d = nn.Dropout2d(p=0.1)

            self.in_channels = in_channels

        def forward(self, x):

            x = self.conv2(x)
            x = self.bn2(x)
            x_out = x + res_x
            return self.dropout2d(F.relu(x_out))
            # return F.relu(x_out)
    
    def __init__(self, name=base_name):
        super().__init__()
        self.name = name
        
        self.first_layer = nn.Sequential(  # 256 - 128

            nn.ReLU(),
            # nn.Dropout2d(p=0.08),
        )

        self.blocks = nn.Sequential(
            # self.Block(in_channels=32),  # 128
            self.Block(in_channels=32, x2_channels=True, x2_stride=True),  # 64
            self.Block(in_channels=64),
            self.Block(in_channels=64, x2_channels=True, x2_stride=True),  # 32
            self.Block(in_channels=128),
            self.Block(in_channels=128, x2_channels=True, x2_stride=True),  # 16
            self.Block(in_channels=256, x2_channels=False, x2_stride=True),  # 8
        )
        
        self.output_layer = nn.Sequential(  # 1
            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1)),
            nn.Flatten()
            # nn.Dropout2d(p=0.08),
        )
        
        self.fc1 = nn.Linear(256, 128)
        self.fc2 = nn.Linear(128, 3)
        self.bn1 = nn.BatchNorm1d(128)
        self.fc_dropout = nn.Dropout(p=0.17)

    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.first_layer(x)
        x = self.blocks(x)
        x = self.output_layer(x)
        x = self.fc_dropout(F.relu(self.bn1(self.fc1(x))))
        logits = self.fc2(x)
        return logits
    
class Model_SqueezeNet(nn.Module):
    # https://medium.com/sfu-cspmp/squeezenet-the-key-to-unlocking-the-potential-of-edge-computing-c8b224d839ba
    # https://github.com/pytorch/vision/blob/main/torchvision/models/squeezenet.py
    # https://arxiv.org/pdf/1602.07360.pdf
    # BatchNorm not in documentation, but it`s required!!!
    class FireBlock(nn.Module):
        def __init__(self, in_channels: int, s1: int, e1: int, e3: int):
            super().__init__()
            self.conv_bottleneck = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=s1, kernel_size=1, padding=0, bias=False)
            self.conv_1x1 = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=s1, out_channels=e1, kernel_size=1, padding=0, bias=False)
            self.conv_3x3 = nn.Conv2d(in_channels=s1, out_channels=e3, kernel_size=3, padding=1, bias=False)
            self.bn_s1 = nn.BatchNorm2d(s1)
            self.bn_e1 = nn.BatchNorm2d(e1)
            self.bn_e3 = nn.BatchNorm2d(e3)

        def forward(self, x_in):
            x_bottle = self.bn_s1(F.relu(self.conv_bottleneck(x_in), inplace=True))
            return torch.cat([self.bn_e1(F.relu(self.conv_1x1(x_bottle), inplace=True)),
                              self.bn_e3(F.relu(self.conv_3x3(x_bottle), inplace=True))], dim=1)

    base_name = "squeeze_net_1.1_another"
    def __init__(self, name=base_name):
        super().__init__()
        self.name = name
        
        self.max_pool_2x2 = nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3, stride=2, ceil_mode=True)
        self.first_layer = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(1, 96, kernel_size=3, stride=2), nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3, stride=2, padding=1),)
        
        self.block1 = Model_SqueezeNet.FireBlock(96, 16, 64, 64)
        self.block2 = Model_SqueezeNet.FireBlock(128, 16, 64, 64)
        
        self.block3 = Model_SqueezeNet.FireBlock(128, 32, 128, 128)
        self.block4 = Model_SqueezeNet.FireBlock(256, 32, 128, 128)
        
        self.block5 = Model_SqueezeNet.FireBlock(256, 48, 192, 192)
        self.block6 = Model_SqueezeNet.FireBlock(384, 48, 192, 192)
        self.block7 = Model_SqueezeNet.FireBlock(384, 64, 256, 256)
        self.block8 = Model_SqueezeNet.FireBlock(512, 64, 256, 256)
        
        self.classifier = nn.Sequential(
            # nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1)),
            nn.Dropout(p=0.6),
            nn.Conv2d(512, 3, kernel_size=1),
            nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1)),
            nn.Flatten(),
        )

    def forward(self, x):
        x = self.first_layer(x)  # 256 -> 64
        x = self.block1(x)
        x = self.block2(x)  # Res
        x = self.max_pool_2x2(x)  # 64 -> 32
        x = self.block3(x)
        x = self.block4(x)  # Res
        x = self.max_pool_2x2(x)  # 64 -> 32
        x = self.block5(x)
        x = self.block6(x)  # Res
        x = self.block7(x)
        x = self.block8(x)  # Res
        logits = self.classifier(x)
        return logits
    
class Model_SqueezeNeXt(nn.Module):
    # https://sh-tsang.medium.com/reading-squeezenext-hardware-aware-neural-network-design-image-classification-3fc8d1d3f76
    # https://github.com/osmr/imgclsmob/blob/c03fa67de3c9e454e9b6d35fe9cbb6b15c28fda7/pytorch/pytorchcv/models/squeezenext.py
    # https://arxiv.org/pdf/1803.10615v2.pdf
    class SqueezeNeXtUnit(nn.Module):
        def __init__(self,
                     in_channels,
                     out_channels,
                     stride):
            super().__init__()
            if stride == 2:
                reduction_den = 1
                self.resize_identity = True
            elif in_channels > out_channels:
                reduction_den = 4
                self.resize_identity = True
            else:
                reduction_den = 2
                self.resize_identity = False
                
            self.use_bias = False
            self.act = nn.ReLU(inplace=True)
            
            self.conv_x5 = nn.Sequential(
                # Conv 1 (1x1)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den),
                          kernel_size=1, bias=self.use_bias, stride=stride),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=(in_channels // reduction_den)), self.act,
                # Conv 2 (1x1)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den), out_channels=(in_channels // (2 * reduction_den)),
                          kernel_size=1, bias=self.use_bias),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=(in_channels // (2 * reduction_den))), self.act,
                # Conv 3 (1x3)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=(in_channels // (2 * reduction_den)), out_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den),
                          kernel_size=(1, 3), padding=(0, 1), bias=self.use_bias),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=(in_channels // reduction_den)), self.act,
                # Conv 4 (3x1)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den), out_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den),
                          kernel_size=(3, 1), padding=(1, 0), bias=self.use_bias),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=(in_channels // reduction_den)), self.act,
                # Conv 5 (1x1)
                nn.Conv2d(in_channels=(in_channels // reduction_den), out_channels=out_channels,
                          kernel_size=1, bias=self.use_bias),
                nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=out_channels), self.act,
            )

            if self.resize_identity:
                self.identity_conv = nn.Sequential(
                    nn.Conv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=out_channels, kernel_size=1,
                              stride=stride, bias=self.use_bias),
                    nn.BatchNorm2d(num_features=out_channels), self.act
                )
    
        def forward(self, x):
            if self.resize_identity:
                identity = self.identity_conv(x)
            else:
                identity = x
            x = self.conv_x5(x)
            x = x + identity
            return self.act(x)

    def __init__(self, name="v1",      # Name iteration of model
                 width_scale=1.,       # Wide of model
                 layers=[2, 4, 14, 1]  # From original SqNxt-23
                 ):
        super().__init__()
        self.name = f"{width_scale:.1f}-SqNxt-{sum(layers)+2}_{name}"
        
        # SqNxt-23v5
        num_classes = 3
        init_block_channels = int(64 * width_scale)
        final_block_channels = int(128 * width_scale)
        channels_per_layers = [32, 64, 128, 256]
        channels = [[int(ci * width_scale)] * li for (ci, li) in zip(channels_per_layers, layers)]
        print(self.name, [init_block_channels], *channels, [final_block_channels])
        
        # Make arch
        self.features = nn.Sequential()
        self.features.add_module("first_block", nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(1, init_block_channels, kernel_size=5, stride=2),
            nn.BatchNorm2d(init_block_channels), nn.ReLU(inplace=True),
            nn.MaxPool2d(kernel_size=3, stride=2, ceil_mode=True),
        ))
        
        in_channels = init_block_channels
        for i, channels_per_stage in enumerate(channels):
            stage = nn.Sequential()
            for j, out_channels in enumerate(channels_per_stage):
                stride = 2 if (j == 0) and (i != 0) else 1
                stage.add_module(f"unit_{j + 1}", Model_SqueezeNeXt.SqueezeNeXtUnit(
                    in_channels=in_channels,
                    out_channels=out_channels,
                    stride=stride))
                in_channels = out_channels
            self.features.add_module(f"stage_{i + 1}", stage)
        
        self.features.add_module("final_block", nn.Sequential(
            nn.Conv2d(in_channels=in_channels, out_channels=final_block_channels, kernel_size=1, bias=True),
            nn.AdaptiveAvgPool2d((1, 1)),
            nn.Flatten()
        ))

        self.output = nn.Sequential(
            nn.Linear(in_features=final_block_channels, out_features=num_classes)
        )

    def forward(self, x):
        x = transform_model_forward(x)
        x = self.features(x)
        x = self.output(x)
        return x
    

from torchvision import models as pretrained_models

class Pretrain_DenseNet(nn.Module):
    base_name = "__PRETRAIN_DenseNet"
    def __init__(self, name=base_name):
        super().__init__()
        self.name = name
        
        self.classifier = nn.Sequential( 
            nn.Linear(in_features=1024, out_features=512), nn.ReLU(), nn.Dropout(0.25),
            nn.Linear(in_features=512, out_features=3))
        
        pretrain_model = pretrained_models.densenet121(weights=pretrained_models.DenseNet121_Weights.DEFAULT).to(device)  # print(pretrain_model)
        for param in pretrain_model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False
    
        pretrain_model.classifier = self.classifier
        self.pretrain_model = pretrain_model

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.pretrain_model(x)

class Pretrain_MobileNet(nn.Module):
    base_name = "__PRETRAIN_MobileNet"
    def __init__(self, name=base_name):
        super().__init__()
        self.name = name
        
        self.classifier = nn.Sequential( 
            nn.Linear(in_features=1280, out_features=512), nn.ReLU(), nn.Dropout(0.25),
            nn.Linear(in_features=512, out_features=3))
        
        pretrain_model = pretrained_models.mobilenet_v2(weights=pretrained_models.MobileNet_V2_Weights.DEFAULT).to(device)  # print(pretrain_model)
        for param in pretrain_model.parameters():
            param.requires_grad = False
    
        pretrain_model.classifier = self.classifier
        self.pretrain_model = pretrain_model

    def forward(self, x):
        return self.pretrain_model(x)
